When building odd contraptions and flying coffins, I get these duplicate parts.

Basically, they're partnamehere with (x2) up to something like (x5) indicating how many times they've been duplicated.

They're inside of eachother, so placing one of these parts will cause issues like clipping and weird shadows. This is on version 0.90

My mod list is as follows:

ART

Aviation Lights

B9 Aerospace

Chatterer

Deadly Reentry

Distant Object Enhancement

Docking Port Alignment

Enhanced Navball

Firespitter

FTT

Karbonite

LLL

Infernal Robotics

MechJeb

MKS

PlanetShine

Real Fuels

Rover Wheel Sounds

SCANsat

SXT

WernherChecker

Bump? If that's allowed at least. Better than a new topic.

Edited February 5, 2015 by sal_vager

Hi kimbokins, we don't usually like to see thread bumping but I can see it was necessary in this case, can you give us more info on the issue please, see the sticky threads on how to find your logs and post them, also pics would be good as we don't know what parts you are having trouble with

The parts with (x5) etc are from B9 and show the different variants of it (LFO/LF/Monoprop, raised/straight etc). If the parts when placed are flickering and clipping, it means your Firespitter plugin is incorrectly installed or out of date.

http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-TuNDZOv8to0/TgjI7mE7_XI/AAAAAAAAATA/9nvTYZdm9ZI/s530/zelda.gif

I've tried literally everything. The only thing I didn't think of, fixed it. Thank you
